T1  - Inflammatory bowel disease is presenting sooner after immigration in more recent US immigrants from Cuba.
T3  - Comment in: Aliment Pharmacol Ther. 2017 Aug;46(4):465-466. doi: 10.1111/apt.14186 PMID: 28707789 [https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28707789] Comment in: Aliment Pharmacol Ther. 2017 Aug;46(4):467. doi: 10.1111/apt.14200 PMID: 28707792 [https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28707792] Comment in: Aliment Pharmacol Ther. 2017 Oct;46(8):768-769. doi: 10.1111/apt.14278 PMID: 28901570 [https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28901570] Comment in: Aliment Pharmacol Ther. 2017 Oct;46(8):768. doi: 10.1111/apt.14249 PMID: 28901571 [https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28901571]
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1111/apt.14145
A1  - Damas, O M
A1  - Avalos, D J
A1  - Palacio, A M
A1  - Gomez, L
A1  - Quintero, M A
A1  - Deshpande, A R
