T1  - [Midwives in Brod na Savi (Croatia) in 19th century].
T2  - O primaljama u Brodu na Savi u XIX. stoljecu.
A1  - Cosic, Vesna
A1  - Fatovic Ferencic, Stella
A1  - Miskic, Blazenka
Y1  - 2015//
N2  - The development of population policy and health legislation as a result of government, the need for more young, healthy, working and military active population, resulted in the education of all health workers including midwives, legal regulation of their work, increasing their number and training of midwifery profession. With the development of this profession conditions of women giving birth, pregnancy and birth control were gradually improved, and thus influenced the birth rate and mortality of the population and the natural growth. On the example of the town of Brod na Savi one can see that it was time-consuming and controlled development of the midwifery profession in the region, which have affected the poor socio-economic conditions, poor climatic conditions, and the presence of the border and the consequent large-scale migration of the population. It is important to note that the foundations for population policies and the observed midwifery profession enabled the development of the same in the coming period.
